Author: Arturo Borrero Gonzalez <arturo.borrero@chainguard.dev>
Bug-Chainguard: https://github.com/chainguard-dev/internal-dev/issues/12556

datadog-agent 7.78 moved eBPF CO-RE / prebuilt compilation from ninja to
Bazel.  The Bazel toolchain downloads a bare `clang-bpf` binary from the
DataDog S3 omnibus mirror but does NOT ship Clang's resource directory
(the one containing `stdarg.h`, `stddef.h`, etc.), so any eBPF source
that pulls in <linux/kernel.h> -> <stdarg.h> fails with
"fatal error: 'stdarg.h' file not found".

This is the Bazel-flow equivalent of the system_probe.py hunk that
fix-7.66.0-ftbfs.patch used to apply for the (now-removed) ninja CO-RE
flow.  We point the eBPF clang invocations at our local /opt/clang's
resource includes, which are populated by the "Install clang-12" step
in the melange pipeline.  The pipeline also disables Bazel sandboxing
so /opt/clang is reachable from inside the build action.

--- a/bazel/rules/ebpf/ebpf.bzl
+++ b/bazel/rules/ebpf/ebpf.bzl
@@ -106,6 +106,7 @@
     if ctx.attr.core:
         clang_args.add("-target", "bpf")
     clang_args.add("-emit-llvm")
+    clang_args.add("-isystem", "/opt/clang/lib/clang/12.0.1/include")
     clang_args.add_all(flags)

     # Include directories from deps
